Michael Dunn (actor) https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_Dunn_(actor) 0 Michael Dunn (born Gary Neil Miller, October 20, 1934 – August 30, 1973) was an American actor and singer. He inspired a number of actors that were smaller and shorter than most average people, including Zelda Rubinstein, Eric The Actor, Mark Povinelli, and Ricardo Gil.
